### 2. The Definition of *Virtù* (Prudence and Capability)
*Virtù* in the Machiavellian and Renaissance sense does not mean moral goodness; it refers to the capacity to act effectively, adapt to circumstances (*fortuna*), and achieve one's goals through skill and prudence.

